gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Rockets 118, Suns 109
gameRecap.excerpt: Houston defeats Phoenix, 118-109. For Houston, Jalen Green led the way with 34 points (six 3PM), nine rebounds, and four assists aided by Fred VanVleet (24 (six 3PM) points, 11 assists), and Alperen Sengun (21 points, 10 rebounds, two steals) in the victory. Kevin Durant led the way with 30 points and nine rebounds while Devin Booker tallied 24 points and five assists for Phoenix in the losing effort. Houston wins and improves to 26-34, while Phoenix moves to 35-25 in the loss.
